{
  "_README": "Canonical, repo-owned BACKUP/NAS JobDto skeleton for File Share Backup. This is the SINGLE maintained source of a valid FSB job shape — runbooks build a NEW job from THIS file (recipe R4c), NOT by cloning any live job (e.g. job 22 on nbr-5). Self-contained: a clean nbr-5 appliance with the file share discovered + an online repo is sufficient. Substitution contract (the only fields a runbook patches): __JOB_NAME__, objects[0].sourceVid=__SOURCE_VID__, objects[0].targetName=__SOURCE_NAME__, objects[0].targetStorageVid=__TARGET_REPO_VID__, objects[0].mappings (leave [] for whole-share scope, or append one {..., sourceIdentifierType:FILE} entry per selected file — see R4c MappingBuilder; FSB is file-level selection only, no FOLDER). Everything else is a validated default; override only via the R4c BackupOptionsBuilder/ScheduleBuilder when a TC requires it. Verified shape against NBR 11.2.1 (build 106316, nbr-5). Remove the _README/_* keys before saveJob (or leave them — NBR ignores unknown top-level keys; prefer removing for cleanliness).",
